This paper focuses on the design of a routing protocol for wireless ad hoc and sensor networks, which falls under the category of networked systems (cs.NI). The paper also discusses the optimization of the network-MAC layer interaction, which involves information theory and communication theory, making cs.IT a likely sub-category. The use of geographic information and cooperative relaying techniques also suggests that the paper could fall under the categories of machine learning (cs.LG) and control systems (cs.SY). Finally, the paper proposes a forwarding scheme based on geographic position, which could be related to spatial data structures and algorithms, making cs.DS a possible sub-category as well.
